data.content:
Here's your test rewritten with specific MSTest 3.x collection assertions:

```csharp
[TestMethod]
public void GetActiveUsers_ReturnsOnlyActiveUsers()
{
    var service = new UserService();
    var users = service.GetActiveUsers();

    Assert.IsNotEmpty(users);
    Assert.IsTrue(users.All(u => u.IsActive));
    Assert.HasCount(3, users);
    Assert.ContainsSingle(users.Where(u => u.Role == "Admin"));
}
```

**Replacements made:**

| Original | Replacement | Why |
|----------|-------------|-----|
| `Assert.IsTrue(users.Count > 0)` | `Assert.IsNotEmpty(users)` | Clearer intent, better failure message |
| `Assert.IsTrue(users.Count() == 3)` | `Assert.HasCount(3, users)` | Shows expected vs actual count on failure |
| `Single()` + null check | `Assert.ContainsSingle(filtered)` | Asserts exactly one match exists |

The `All()` predicate doesn't have a direct assertion equivalent, so `Assert.IsTrue` is fine there.

These require **MSTest 3.8+** (`<PackageReference Include="MSTest" Version="3.8.2" />`).
